WEBVTT

00:00.386 --> 00:01.168
Thank you, James.

00:01.228 --> 00:04.455
I felt the need to run up just to display my tick-a-like energy.

00:04.495 --> 00:07.522
What an introduction.

00:07.562 --> 00:10.489
It's great, great to be able to share with you this morning.

00:10.529 --> 00:13.816
And I've loved our dedications today.

00:13.876 --> 00:15.139
That's been beautiful.

00:15.199 --> 00:18.226
This message has been

00:18.914 --> 00:45.394
It has, it's been like a big old fountain inside of me that is just bursting to come out today and it's been a funny thing because when I first began to study for it, when I first began to get the download a few weeks ago, I was in the office and I was so excited about it that I was jumping around, I was like a big contagious ball of energy and then life was kind of crept in

00:45.506 --> 00:49.432
And I began to read a few more commentaries, and I really love studying.

00:49.472 --> 00:52.817
I'm a total geek, so I was reading more and more and more.

00:52.957 --> 01:09.682
And then as I sat down to put all of these kind of beautiful fountains of excitement and knowledge and Holy Spirit revelation together, every time I try to come up with this structure, oh, it was so boring.

01:10.018 --> 01:13.764
I started reading it back and it felt like I was reading a textbook.

01:14.205 --> 01:25.543
It felt like I was reading actually one of my dissertations from university, which was a very interesting read, but possibly would cause about 90% of you to exit the building if I made you read it.

01:25.603 --> 01:35.218
So my prayer this morning is that beyond the bullet points that I have now reduced it down to you, what you would capture today

01:35.362 --> 01:39.028
is directly from Holy Spirit into your heart.

01:39.048 --> 01:41.973
So I'm going to pray because I really need that this morning.

01:45.078 --> 01:55.335
Jesus, sometimes we cannot contain in three neat, alliterated points what you want to do and say and reveal amongst us.

01:56.978 --> 02:01.746
And so I pray this morning that that which you gave to me

02:02.562 --> 02:09.655
I would faithfully deliver to your precious people this morning, those in the building, those joining online.

02:11.238 --> 02:19.633
Father, I pray that not one person would miss out on the fountains of living water that you have for us today.

02:20.414 --> 02:21.456
So would you annoy me?

02:21.496 --> 02:23.339
Would you help me?

02:23.500 --> 02:25.664
Would you speak through me and in spite of me?

02:26.585 --> 02:27.026
Amen.

02:28.354 --> 02:32.097
Well, the invitation came, didn't it, on Vision Sunday?

02:32.398 --> 02:51.394
We as a church are in our centenary year, and there's lots to be excited for, but we really feel it's time for each of us to step into the story that God is writing in and through us, and the story that He wants to write for the next 100 years.

02:51.974 --> 02:58.340
Everybody in this room and joining us online, we all have a part to play in that narrative.

02:58.320 --> 03:22.162
nobody is on the margins or excluded and we have this sense that there is new glory for us to experience the heavy weighty presence of God that changes hearts and changes lives but we also have this sense that as we experience His glory there is new life

03:22.306 --> 03:29.654
that is springing up and I am encouraged to say that those signs of life are really evident in our midst at the moment.

03:29.815 --> 03:33.959
It's hugely exciting to see what God is doing.

03:35.241 --> 03:46.674
Bev Murrell followed up with an incredible talk about systems and wells, no, systems and springs.

03:46.946 --> 03:59.579
She was talking about us not drawing from these man-made structures that are contained with stagnant water, but drawing from the source of all life itself from Jesus.

03:59.619 --> 04:06.726
And I'm mentioning and referring back to that because it's really pertinent for what I would like to share today.

04:06.786 --> 04:15.154
Now, when we moved into our house about 14 years ago now, one of the things that really

04:15.298 --> 04:18.602
cracked me up on our first ever morning in our new house.

04:18.702 --> 04:27.633
Is it Pete went into the bathroom and he was taking a shower and all I could hear was this crazy laughter.

04:28.073 --> 04:29.936
He was laughing out loud.

04:30.016 --> 04:32.679
He was laughing and laughing and laughing.

04:33.560 --> 04:37.485
So when he finally came out, I was like, what was making you laugh?

04:37.505 --> 04:41.970
And he went, you will not believe how powerful that shower is.

04:42.114 --> 04:43.436
And this matters, right?

04:43.577 --> 04:50.168
It matters because the house that we had been living with, living in, it took you so long to wash long hair.

04:50.188 --> 04:52.632
It was like a little trickle of water.

04:52.672 --> 04:55.016
There was no deluge or power behind it.

04:55.497 --> 05:07.858
And so the contrast between our old house and our new people are nodding at me because you know there are some living in this room and you know what it feels like to stand under a shower and wish that you could get your hair wet.

05:08.034 --> 05:10.818
this shower, it's so powerful.

05:10.878 --> 05:13.923
And he was, he was just overjoyed.

05:14.143 --> 05:19.111
He was absolutely overjoyed by the power of this water.

05:19.131 --> 05:22.996
I know, I mean, we're easy.

05:23.056 --> 05:25.119
We're easy to please in our, in our family.

05:25.680 --> 05:32.210
But as I have been praying for us since the start of the year,

05:32.610 --> 05:43.186
I just keep seeing the same picture and every time I pray for the church I see this auditorium and I see

05:43.618 --> 05:47.822
these fountains springing up in different places.

05:48.342 --> 05:53.627
And I'm not talking a nice sprinkly Rome style fountain, my friends.

05:54.327 --> 05:58.091
I am talking the kind of eruption of water.

05:58.531 --> 06:01.934
I think they call them geezers, and we feel right at home in Essex saying that, don't we?

06:02.394 --> 06:13.604
Geezers, they're these kind of bursts of water, and they are so powerful that I reckon if you were standing underneath, you'd be propelled into midair, that kind of thing.

06:13.584 --> 06:34.803
seeing them, springing up in different places in the auditorium and then the water begins to hydrate and refresh everybody around it until there is so much water that it begins to stream like a river out of the building and into the surrounding area.

06:37.265 --> 06:42.610
There is an invitation that heaven wants to extend to you and to me today.

06:44.002 --> 06:48.548
to step into a season of living water.

06:49.549 --> 06:52.914
Drawn from the source and not from the system.

06:52.934 --> 06:56.339
And I want to take a look at living water today.

06:56.359 --> 06:59.162
And I'm going to be majoring on a passage in John.

06:59.202 --> 07:01.946
If you have your Bible, I love you to follow with me.

07:01.966 --> 07:07.974
I haven't put it onto slides because it's 42 verses, which is a lot to put onto slides.

07:08.395 --> 07:10.898
So please follow with me, John 4.

07:11.106 --> 07:16.835
I'm reading from verse 1 to 42 and I'll try and do it as fast as I can without putting you off.

07:17.336 --> 07:17.877
Are you ready?

07:19.179 --> 07:19.519
Are you ready?

07:20.301 --> 07:21.202
Come on then, let's do it.

07:23.125 --> 07:29.195
Now, Jesus learned that the Pharisees had heard that he was gaining and baptizing more disciples than John.

07:29.616 --> 07:33.682
Although, in fact, it was not Jesus who baptized but his disciples.

07:33.762 --> 07:37.446
So, he left Judea and went back once more to Galilee.

07:37.907 --> 07:40.350
Now, he had to go through Samaria.

07:40.810 --> 07:43.293
So, he came to a town in Samaria called Sicka.

07:43.894 --> 07:47.718
Near the plot of ground, Jacob had given to his son, Joseph.

07:48.218 --> 07:53.545
Jacob's well was there, and Jesus, tired as he was from the journey, sat down by the well.

07:54.345 --> 07:56.668
It was about noon, hold that thought.

07:57.008 --> 08:01.874
When a Samaritan woman came to draw water, Jesus said to her, will you give me a drink?

08:02.082 --> 08:04.565
His disciples had gone into the town to buy food.

08:05.185 --> 08:10.732
The Samaritan women said to him, you are a Jew and I am a Samaritan woman.

08:11.412 --> 08:14.095
How can you ask me for a drink?

08:14.516 --> 08:17.479
For Jews do not associate with Samaritans.

08:18.440 --> 08:30.834
Jesus answered her, if you knew the gift of God and who it is that asks you for a drink, you would have asked him and he would have given you living water.

08:32.226 --> 08:41.720
Are you greater than our father, Jacob, who gave us the well and drank from it himself, as did also his sons and his livestock?

08:43.162 --> 08:48.750
Jesus answered, everyone who drinks this water will be thirsty again.

08:49.612 --> 08:54.098
But whoever drinks the water, I give them will never thirst.

08:54.539 --> 09:01.970
Indeed, the water I give them will become in them a spring of water, welling up to eternal life.

09:02.530 --> 09:09.979
The woman said to him, sir, give me this water so that I won't get thirsty and have to keep humming here to draw water.

09:10.039 --> 09:13.744
He told her, go, call your husband and come back.

09:14.445 --> 09:15.907
I have no husband, she replied.

09:16.307 --> 09:19.811
Jesus said to her, you are right when you say you have no husband.

09:20.132 --> 09:25.438
The fact is you have had five husbands and the man you now have is not your husband.

09:25.719 --> 09:28.222
What you have just said is quite true.

09:29.964 --> 09:31.506
Sir, the woman said,

09:31.810 --> 09:33.432
I can see that you're a prophet.

09:34.093 --> 09:41.143
Our ancestors worshipped on this mountain, but you Jews claim that the place where we must worship is in Jerusalem.

09:42.745 --> 09:45.829
Women, Jesus replied, believe me.

09:46.530 --> 09:52.918
A time is coming when you will worship the Father, neither on this mountain nor in Jerusalem.

09:53.279 --> 09:56.083
You Samaritans worship what you do not know.

09:56.103 --> 10:01.490
We worship what we do know for salvation is from the Jews, yet

10:01.986 --> 10:15.243
A time is coming and has now come when the true worshipers will worship the Father in spirits and in truth, for they are the kind of worshipers the Father seeks.

10:15.843 --> 10:22.131
God is spirit and his worshipers must worship in the spirits and in truth.

10:23.373 --> 10:27.238
The woman said, I know that Messiah called Christ is coming.

10:27.758 --> 10:30.802
When he comes, he will explain everything to us.

10:31.586 --> 10:38.694
Then Jesus declared, I, the one speaking to you, I am he.

10:39.875 --> 10:47.404
Just then his disciples returned and were surprised to find him talking with a woman, but no one asked, what do you want?

10:47.724 --> 10:49.346
Or why are you talking with her?

10:49.987 --> 10:53.351
Then leaving her water jar, hold that thought.

10:53.731 --> 10:59.858
The woman went back to the town and said to the people, come see a man who told me

10:59.970 --> 11:01.513
everything I've ever done.

11:02.134 --> 11:03.658
Could this be the Messiah?

11:04.179 --> 11:07.064
They came out of the town and made their way towards Him.

11:07.646 --> 11:11.894
Meanwhile, His disciples urged Him, Rabbi, eat something.

11:12.576 --> 11:17.105
But He said to them, I have food to eat that you know nothing about.

11:17.125 --> 11:21.554
Then His disciples said to each other, could someone have brought Him food?

11:22.114 --> 11:27.801
My food said Jesus is to do the will of him who sent me and to finish his work.

11:27.821 --> 11:30.985
Don't you have a saying, it's still four months until harvest.

11:31.506 --> 11:37.794
I tell you, open your eyes, look at the fields, they are ripe for harvest.

11:38.935 --> 11:47.346
Even now the one who reaps draws a wage and harvests a crop for eternal life so that the sower and the reaper may be glad together.

11:48.290 --> 11:50.893
I'm just going to move on to verse 39.

11:51.293 --> 11:56.399
Many of the Samaritans from that town believed in him because of the women's testimony.

11:56.940 --> 11:59.222
He told me everything I've ever done.

11:59.883 --> 12:05.490
So when the Samaritans came to him, they urged him to stay with them and he stayed two days.

12:06.190 --> 12:11.056
And because of his words, many more became believers.

12:12.257 --> 12:12.818
Wow.

12:12.930 --> 12:15.253
what an incredible passage.

12:15.293 --> 12:22.962
And if you've been around church for any length of time, you have probably heard that passage several times before.

12:23.723 --> 12:30.530
And I think part of what has tied me in knots is that there is just so much in there that I would love the time to unpack.

12:30.891 --> 12:34.735
But the truth is I'm going to take probably a slightly different angle in places.

12:34.996 --> 12:39.581
And that is, you know, it's to the detriment of some other things, but I think that's okay.

12:40.202 --> 12:40.562
So,

12:41.250 --> 12:51.600
First up, I want to give us a bit of context, because this beautiful encounter between Jesus and the Samaritan women takes place at Jacob's Well.

12:52.521 --> 13:06.694
Now, interestingly, when we think back to Bev's talk about systems and springs, Jacob's Well in the Greek is actually described as a freya.

13:07.455 --> 13:08.316
A freya.

13:08.736 --> 13:10.418
And that means a pit.

13:10.882 --> 13:17.971
or a cistern, as opposed to a piggy, which would be a spring or a fountain.

13:18.892 --> 13:25.701
Commentaries tell us that this well largely functioned as a cistern, and this is no mistake.

13:26.322 --> 13:38.898
Here is Jesus, the source of living water, the fountain, the spring itself sitting by a man-made cistern.

13:39.298 --> 13:44.746
Secondly, this encounter took place in the bright noonday sun.

13:44.766 --> 13:54.400
This matters not only because it tells us a lot about the Samaritan women and many of us will have heard that it's likely she was ostracized.

13:55.000 --> 14:04.594
It was likely that she's a woman with a history and she probably came to that well alone.

14:05.218 --> 14:16.135
Because she didn't have that community of women to go with for whatever reason, she was a lonely, vulnerable, perhaps even victimized women.

14:17.658 --> 14:24.689
Normally women would travel for safety and culturally appropriate reasons in groups to the well.

14:25.971 --> 14:33.042
But it's also really interesting because it's a direct contrast to chapter three

14:33.506 --> 14:39.174
and an encounter that Jesus has with a very important religious leader named Nicodemus.

14:39.234 --> 14:41.537
Now this guy, he's in the Sanhedrin.

14:41.577 --> 14:50.290
He's a really important Jewish leader, but he seeks Jesus out under cover of nightfall.

14:51.251 --> 14:51.632
Why?

14:51.652 --> 14:54.355
He's afraid of risking his reputation.

14:54.696 --> 14:58.621
He's afraid to be associated with Jesus, even though he's curious.

14:58.942 --> 15:01.906
This is a man who knows there must be more

15:02.786 --> 15:05.191
But under cover of night, he approaches.

15:05.611 --> 15:11.202
And interestingly, Nicodemus leaves that encounter still in spiritual darkness.

15:11.623 --> 15:16.612
He's on a journey, but he does not yet believe that Jesus is the Messiah.

15:16.973 --> 15:26.290
And that picture of darkness is important because it not only describes the cover of nightfall, but it describes the confusion in his heart.

15:26.818 --> 15:29.803
Contrast that with a Samaritan woman.

15:30.123 --> 15:31.225
She is not a Jew.

15:31.746 --> 15:33.048
She is not a leader.

15:33.368 --> 15:36.974
She is not somebody considered important culturally.

15:37.054 --> 15:40.119
She is a woman and a Samaritan.

15:41.601 --> 15:53.359
And Jesus seeks out an encounter with her in the noonday sun, the brightest, lightest, hottest part of the day.

15:53.419 --> 15:55.282
Isn't that incredible?

15:56.322 --> 15:59.988
Jesus has an appointment with this woman.

16:00.829 --> 16:10.364
And it's the most incredible contrast between the two, this night and day moment that is about to transpire for this beautiful woman.

16:10.784 --> 16:20.059
And unlike Nicodemus, she gets the memo from Jesus and she believes that he's the son of God and she is radically transformed.

16:20.540 --> 16:24.626
She heads away back to her city as the first

16:24.738 --> 16:27.322
ever woman preacher of the good news.

16:27.603 --> 16:30.046
How groundbreaking and radical is that?

16:30.667 --> 16:31.008
Yes.

16:32.510 --> 16:39.341
Oh, there's so much I could share and could give to you about that Samaritan woman.

16:39.862 --> 16:47.314
But I don't want to go there today because I want us to think about living water in this passage.

16:47.354 --> 16:52.402
You see, this woman, she comes to draw water.

16:55.970 --> 17:02.379
that will satiate her physical thirst for a short time.

17:03.521 --> 17:05.484
This is not living water.

17:06.826 --> 17:08.368
It's cistern water.

17:08.989 --> 17:09.790
It's stagnant.

17:10.251 --> 17:11.492
It's a little bit stale.

17:12.414 --> 17:15.899
And it will quench her thirst temporarily.

17:16.960 --> 17:20.585
But very soon she's going to need to return to that well again.

17:20.626 --> 17:23.730
Interesting.

17:23.970 --> 17:31.821
that the jar that she has brought is going to be enough for her and possibly a few others.

17:31.901 --> 17:33.503
In fact, she even mentions that.

17:33.624 --> 17:38.230
She talks about Jacob's well and how it was good for him and his household.

17:38.811 --> 17:45.440
But this jar is never going to be able to satiate the thirst of a whole city.

17:45.961 --> 17:47.303
It's enough for me and mine.

17:48.204 --> 17:49.586
That's important.

17:50.082 --> 17:55.198
And everyone who drinks this water will be thirsty again.

17:55.218 --> 17:58.467
The thirst is real.

18:00.453 --> 18:03.282
There are people all around us thirsty.

18:03.362 --> 18:04.203
for something more.

18:04.684 --> 18:10.252
Maybe even you and I are sitting here today wondering if this is all there is to life.

18:10.672 --> 18:16.180
We get up, we're on a conveyor belt or a treadmill or whichever image you would like to use.

18:16.601 --> 18:31.922
And we're thirsty for something more and yet somehow we seem to fill our lives, fill our spirits, fill our minds with that which never truly satisfies and we have to keep going back and back again for more.

18:33.762 --> 18:36.146
but we don't feel satiated.

18:41.674 --> 18:59.122
And here is Jesus, the source of living water, sitting by the well and offering her something greater, something life-changing, something life-giving, something that will truly satisfy

19:00.162 --> 19:07.049
He can see that this woman is thirsty for more than the stagnant, stale, well water in front of her.

19:07.589 --> 19:11.933
There is a spiritual thirst that nothing has touched.

19:12.614 --> 19:14.476
Something is missing.

19:20.802 --> 19:29.170
And Jesus says, whoever drinks the water I give will never thirst.

19:30.626 --> 19:31.949
And it's a no brainer for her.

19:31.989 --> 19:35.597
She says, give me this water so that I will not get thirsty.

19:35.617 --> 19:38.263
And she's probably still thinking about her body.

19:39.947 --> 19:42.653
But they have this incredible exchange.

19:43.535 --> 19:49.970
And Jesus suddenly reveals her identity first and foremost.

19:50.082 --> 20:16.178
the things in her life where she's been filled with other things and actually they're things that have broken her systems and structures that have been so rigid that she has been oppressed and downtrodden and he speaks into the core and the essence and the heart of who she is and he truly sees her in that moment but then he reveals his

20:16.354 --> 20:17.255
identity.

20:17.696 --> 20:29.513
And he tells this Samaritan woman, double disqualification, Samaritan woman, that he is the Messiah.

20:29.934 --> 20:31.876
That is mind-blowing.

20:32.477 --> 20:44.114
And it's like this Taddah moment as a woman who has been written off by society, by her culture, maybe even by herself, but that is me speculating on the text.

20:44.322 --> 20:49.290
is written in to the greatest story ever told.

20:50.231 --> 20:50.812
Wow!

20:51.633 --> 20:52.615
That blows my mind.

20:59.205 --> 21:03.271
But this for me is the crux of where I'm going with this today.

21:08.680 --> 21:09.421
She has changed.

21:11.384 --> 21:12.626
She dares to believe.

21:13.026 --> 21:15.071
that Jesus is who he says he is.

21:15.111 --> 21:28.786
And as that transformation process takes place, as she puts her trust in him, that which has temporarily sufficed to meet

21:28.866 --> 21:43.570
her ongoing thirst, that which represents the rigidity, the the finite, the temporal, the stuff that is here today but we're going to have to keep coming back again and again and it never truly quenches that

21:43.618 --> 21:47.182
ache inside is left behind.

21:47.682 --> 21:50.986
She leaves behind her water jar.

21:51.386 --> 21:52.668
And this really matters.

21:52.728 --> 21:55.110
And honestly, I've never noticed that before.

21:55.611 --> 22:01.537
I've noticed so many other things about this passage, but this is so significant.

22:02.138 --> 22:05.782
Why has she left her water jar behind?

22:06.182 --> 22:09.746
Well, that's because she doesn't need it anymore.

22:10.082 --> 22:22.601
She doesn't need the cyst and man-made well water that keeps her contained, that causes her to have to keep coming back again and again from this place of insatiable thirst.

22:22.961 --> 22:26.547
Because she's standing on the fountain of living water.

22:26.607 --> 22:33.677
It's springing up inside of her and it is bursting out of her and she no longer needs that container.

22:33.697 --> 22:36.882
Wow.

22:38.306 --> 22:59.710
she leaves the jar behind because she has found something that will permanently satisfy, something that is so abundant that it will flow out from her and into the whole of her city, something far greater than the water that she has been sustained by hitherto.

22:59.750 --> 23:03.634
The jar she leaves behind

23:04.098 --> 23:12.367
represents so many things, but I wonder what the jar might represent for you and me today, living in the times that we do.

23:12.387 --> 23:18.014
How often do we rely on ourselves, I wonder?

23:19.115 --> 23:25.322
How much of our life is designed to satisfy and gratify ourselves?

23:27.665 --> 23:28.626
We work.

23:28.994 --> 23:33.722
so that we can have more things, so that we can do more things and please don't get me wrong.

23:34.103 --> 23:35.946
That is not wrong in and of itself.

23:36.587 --> 23:49.650
But if we are on this constant treadmill to gratify our own needs, to satisfy ourselves, if we live our lives so focused on that which will sustain me and possibly mine,

23:49.890 --> 23:53.659
We are missing out on the purpose of living water.

23:53.719 --> 24:03.221
And the truth is that this is a woman who didn't know about living water, but most of us sitting in this room today, we do know about living water.

24:04.324 --> 24:06.930
And yet, we feel ourselves

24:06.978 --> 24:13.448
up with stagnant, stale, dank water that will never suffice.

24:13.948 --> 24:16.272
And we wonder why we're kicking around church.

24:16.492 --> 24:17.834
We've heard all the sermons.

24:18.255 --> 24:19.437
We've read all the books.

24:19.797 --> 24:23.182
We've listened to the podcast, but we're still thirsty for more.

24:23.543 --> 24:23.943
Why?

24:23.983 --> 24:26.187
Because we're missing the living water.

24:26.667 --> 24:33.678
Church, we need to leave our jars behind because there is only one source of living water.

24:34.058 --> 24:36.562
And his name is Jesus.

24:37.122 --> 24:42.128
And that is the difference between a system and a spring.

24:44.330 --> 24:51.779
Why do we settle for well water when we have access to the source of living water himself?

24:52.320 --> 25:04.594
Why do we continue to live our lives in a rigid and restricted place containing and confining the living water of God's spirit into a small man-made jar?

25:04.930 --> 25:16.530
heads down, survival mode, working hard, having to come back depleted when we were designed to be channels, freely flowing fountains.

25:20.396 --> 25:22.419
Are you thirsty for more than this?

25:22.460 --> 25:28.690
There's a difference between existing and being alive.

25:29.442 --> 25:35.994
There's a difference between well water in a jar and fountains of living water.

25:36.354 --> 25:51.762
You see, one is rigid and finite, and one is free and flowing, abundant, refreshing, teeming with life and designed to give life to far more than just little old me.

25:53.325 --> 25:54.066
And I feel

25:54.818 --> 25:57.862
that one of the Moses is dead moments.

25:57.882 --> 26:02.409
Do you remember on Vision Sunday, we talked about a new church rising, a new era.

26:02.889 --> 26:07.736
Moses is dead, now you, and that's you and me, it's all of us.

26:08.838 --> 26:20.914
But I think that one of the metaphorical Moses is dead moments is that it's time for us here at Skylark Church to leave behind our jars of self-sufficiency.

26:21.796 --> 26:23.538
God is calling us

26:24.034 --> 26:43.720
to be that generation of believers who won't settle for our own superficial and self-serving systems, but who will draw the supernatural abundance sustaining spring of living water from the source that is found in Jesus.

26:44.682 --> 26:54.034
And this water is not only going to benefit us, it's going to benefit everyone around us.

26:54.242 --> 26:58.208
The water is not just intended for you and for me.

26:58.248 --> 27:05.019
The people left the city and they were coming to him.

27:05.079 --> 27:07.082
This woman, she leaves her jar.

27:07.643 --> 27:14.233
She takes that living water and she begins to overflow and offer it to all those around her.

27:14.734 --> 27:17.658
And they're like, wow, you are so different.

27:17.979 --> 27:20.082
What on earth has happened to you?

27:20.290 --> 27:21.933
And she's saying, this could be the Messiah.

27:21.953 --> 27:24.117
This guy, he told me everything I ever did.

27:24.578 --> 27:30.189
And something about this living water inside of her, it flows and it touches their hearts.

27:30.589 --> 27:33.034
And before you know it, here they come.

27:33.916 --> 27:35.378
They're coming towards Jesus.

27:35.559 --> 27:41.650
Most of the city are approaching because they want to find the source for themselves.

27:42.882 --> 27:46.889
Living water is not designed just for you, my friends.

27:47.350 --> 27:49.594
It's designed for all those around us.

27:49.954 --> 28:03.378
We are called to be channels of peace, channels of grace, channels of healing, channels of comfort, channels of his glory and channels of the good news of his kingdom.

28:03.426 --> 28:11.221
So there's this moment and all of the Samaritans are coming towards Jesus and they want to discover the source for themselves.

28:11.562 --> 28:15.229
But there's this beautiful word that cuts across the moment.

28:15.971 --> 28:23.666
Meanwhile, meanwhile, back in Gotham City, meanwhile, the disciples rock up.

28:24.226 --> 28:33.602
And they raise an eyebrow because it's really unorthodox that Jesus is having this conversation with a woman and they don't like to ask anything about it as we read.

28:34.143 --> 28:39.813
But they miss the moment.

28:40.414 --> 28:41.456
They miss the moment.

28:42.498 --> 28:49.330
They are so focused on very helpfully feeding Jesus' physical body

28:49.634 --> 28:51.176
They want to give him something to eat.

28:51.236 --> 28:52.358
They want to look after him.

28:52.418 --> 28:53.840
That is part of their job.

28:54.140 --> 28:54.721
That's good.

28:54.761 --> 28:57.305
They're trying to serve him to make sure he doesn't burn out.

28:57.785 --> 28:58.747
All of that matters.

28:59.268 --> 29:13.828
But they miss the moment because their head is so focused on the detail, on the rigid, on the structure, on the physical that they can't see this incredible spiritual moment that is unfolding before their eyes.

29:14.589 --> 29:18.034
All these people coming towards Jesus thirsty,

29:18.562 --> 29:20.884
for his life-giving water.

29:20.944 --> 29:24.808
And Jesus, he explains that.

29:24.849 --> 29:27.151
He's like, dude, you've missed the point here.

29:28.352 --> 29:30.975
I've got food that you know nothing about.

29:31.515 --> 29:34.619
My food is to do the will of him who sent me.

29:36.040 --> 29:37.622
And he says, lift up your eyes.

29:38.863 --> 29:41.186
In other words, stop looking at the micro.

29:41.886 --> 29:42.847
Lift up your eyes.

29:43.568 --> 29:45.490
The harvest is all around you.

29:45.826 --> 29:59.061
I know that this doesn't look like harvest time in the natural, but in the spiritual, there is a harvest and you're going to miss it if all you can see is your own physical needs.

30:02.485 --> 30:09.893
Church, there's a difference between being filled and being fulfilled.

30:10.554 --> 30:13.938
And when I talk about filled, I mean physically filled.

30:14.210 --> 30:16.112
We need food and drink to survive.

30:16.572 --> 30:19.615
We need jobs and money and all of those other things.

30:20.016 --> 30:31.867
But sometimes we are in danger of filling up with so much stuff that never fulfills us that we miss this incredible kingdom vista around us.

30:32.447 --> 30:43.698
I don't know about you, but I don't want to miss the moment because we are in a moment of time where we are poised as the people of God to be those channels of love

30:44.226 --> 30:45.488
like never before.

30:46.690 --> 30:48.873
Let's not miss the moment.

30:51.557 --> 30:52.518
A woman changed.

30:53.820 --> 30:55.222
A city changed.

30:56.323 --> 31:09.362
Those previously written off, written in, all because she received the living water that is Jesus and carried it back to those around her.

31:10.466 --> 31:15.493
The end of the text tells us that many Samaritans believed in him and trusted in him.

31:16.054 --> 31:17.697
And then they urged him to stay.

31:17.737 --> 31:21.222
They didn't want to let go of the living water that they had found.

31:21.662 --> 31:27.811
And many more people believed in him with a deep abiding trust.

31:30.936 --> 31:32.999
So how about us today?

31:33.019 --> 31:37.906
I wonder if anyone is thirsty in this room.

31:38.466 --> 31:46.875
Perhaps you have spent all you have on things that fill you, but can never fulfill you.

31:48.076 --> 32:08.338
Perhaps you've encountered the living water of Jesus, but like the disciples, your head has been down on the minutiae, on survival mode, on doing what needs to be done, that you are missing this glorious life-giving spiritual picture that is all around you.

32:13.442 --> 32:15.324
It's time to leave our jars behind.

32:16.526 --> 32:21.352
The Holy Spirit cannot be contained in a man-made water jar.

32:22.313 --> 32:27.980
It's time to stop laboring and striving for that which does not truly satisfy.

32:28.721 --> 32:42.418
It's time to stop settling for stagnant stale water from our own systems and jars and to start drawing directly from the source of living water that is Jesus himself

32:43.650 --> 32:54.665
It's time to stop coming back to the well again and again and to become those fountains of living water for others around us.

32:57.289 --> 33:12.690
We are a product of our consumer generation and so often we settle for me and mine when we are designed to be the light and the life to all around us.

33:15.938 --> 33:18.041
I want to invite us to stand in this moment.

33:39.512 --> 33:44.018
I'm just going to leave us in silence whilst we do this part because I don't want

33:44.834 --> 33:46.916
anything to feel kind of emotionally hyped.

33:50.100 --> 34:05.096
But I just know that Jesus wants to meet our thirst today with the living water of his presence and his spirit.

34:08.139 --> 34:14.386
And if you're here today and you feel like you have tried everything and you're exhausted

34:15.074 --> 34:22.261
and you're depleted and you don't feel like your life in Christ is alive and vibrant.

34:23.362 --> 34:31.611
Can I put it to you that this might be a moment to simply receive the living waters?

34:31.711 --> 34:32.832
It can't be earned.

34:33.412 --> 34:34.654
You'll never be good enough.

34:35.394 --> 34:37.396
You can't work hard enough for it.

34:38.417 --> 34:43.122
It is a beautiful gift from our Father in heaven.

34:44.514 --> 34:57.448
And the linchpin, believing, all you have to do is reach out in your heart and believe that he is who he says he is.

35:04.014 --> 35:11.282
Perhaps you could imagine your jar today, the cistern from which you have been drawing.

35:13.474 --> 35:25.347
And perhaps you could imagine yourself leaving it behind in pursuit of the living water that truly transforms.

35:29.472 --> 35:42.546
If today you would like to receive that living water, whether you have been a Christian for 90 years or whether you are not even a Christian yet,

35:43.458 --> 35:47.443
The invitation from heaven is for every single one of us.

35:48.485 --> 35:59.760
If you would like to receive living waters, I'm simply going to ask you, as a sign of that, just to pop your hands out openly in front of you, and I would love to pray for you today.

36:12.296 --> 36:13.458
Thank you, God.

36:16.514 --> 36:17.235
we need you.

36:18.957 --> 36:19.979
Please forgive us.

36:20.880 --> 36:37.823
Please forgive us for the times that we keep our head down, focused on survival, focus on the physical, focused on acquiring more, trying to satiate our thirst with things that will never truly fulfill us.

36:39.765 --> 36:43.410
Right now, I pray Holy Spirit

36:44.066 --> 36:49.025
you would fill each one of us with your living water.

36:49.848 --> 36:54.706
That as we believe in our hearts, that Jesus is the Son of God.

36:55.330 --> 37:21.242
that we would receive that life-giving water, and I pray that fountains of living water would spring up in each of us, not just for ourselves, for a goose bump or an encounter, but for the benefit of our city and our world, that we would be those channels that flow out and offer life-giving water to all those around us.

37:22.003 --> 37:24.146
Lord, we

37:24.226 --> 37:25.488
need you.

37:25.528 --> 37:42.329
Forgive our self-sufficiency, forgive our self-reliance and I pray that you would teach us to live each day as those fountains let the rivers of living water flow in us and through us.

37:44.752 --> 37:46.354
So come Holy Spirit.

